### 3. Core Features & User Flows

#### 3.1 Onboarding & Pre-Assessment (MVP Priority)
- Welcome + short science explainer (2–3 screens or interactive cards).
- Optional quick profile (age group, goals: child/adult, focus areas).
- **Pre-Assessment**: 20–40 item relational test (similar format to training but diagnostic). Measures baseline accuracy + response time.
- Results screen: “Relational Skill Score” (e.g., 42/100) + estimated cognitive profile + motivation message.
- “Start Your 8–12 Week Program” CTA.

#### 3.2 Training Engine (The Heart of the App)
This is the most critical component for agentic building.

**Key Requirements**:
- **Data-driven stages**: All content defined in JSON (or Room entities) so agents/content creators can expand without code changes.
- **Flexible relation engine**: Support multiple frames (Same/Different, More/Less, Opposite, Before/After, Contains/Within, and combinations).
- **Trial Structure**:
  - Display 1–4 premise statements (beautiful cards or connected graph visualization).
  - Clear Yes/No question on derived relation.
  - Large, thumb-friendly Yes/No buttons + haptic feedback.
  - 20–40 second time limit per trial (configurable).
  - Immediate animated feedback (correct = green + subtle celebration; incorrect = red + brief explanation or “try to derive it”).
- **Block Structure**:
  - Training block (feedback + mastery tracking).
  - Test block (no feedback, accuracy gate e.g. ≥85%).
- **Progression**: Linear or adaptive (unlock next stage on mastery). 50–100+ stages planned.
- **Stimuli Options** (for engagement):
  - Text (nonsense syllables) – faithful to original.
  - Visual (colored abstract shapes, icons, procedurally generated symbols) – recommended enhancement.
  - Mixed mode.

**Adaptive Elements**:
- Performance-based difficulty (accuracy + speed).
- Spaced repetition for weak relations.
- Optional “Focus Mode” for specific frames.

#### 3.3 Gamification & Engagement (Critical for Retention)
- XP / Level system tied to stages completed + accuracy + speed.
- Daily streak + “Daily Challenge” (short curated set).
- Badges/achievements (e.g., “Master of Opposition”, “Fluent Deriver”, “30-Day Streak”).
- Session summary: Accuracy %, Avg response time, Relations strengthened, “Cognitive Gain Estimate”.
- Progress dashboard with beautiful charts (relational skill over time, stage completion heatmap).
- Optional light social: Anonymous leaderboards or “compare to average user” (privacy-first).

#### 3.4 Post-Training & Insights
- Post-assessment (same format as pre, different items).
- Detailed before/after report + “Your relational reasoning improved X%”.
- Personalized recommendations (“You strengthened comparison relations — great for math/problem-solving”).
- Exportable progress report (PDF).

#### 3.5 Other Features
- **Settings**: Theme (light/dark + high contrast), sound/haptics, text size, stimuli style (text vs visual), session length preference, notifications.
- **Accessibility**: Full TalkBack support, scalable fonts, color-blind friendly palettes, reduced motion option.
- **Offline-first**: Everything works without internet after

